# Response Handling Templates

## Sealed Interface Pattern (Java 17+)

All generated response interfaces use Java sealed types:

```java
// Generated - DO NOT EDIT
public interface UserApiResponses {

    sealed interface GetUserApiResponse {
        record GetUser200ApiResponse(UserResponseTO content) implements GetUserApiResponse {}
        record GetUser404ApiResponse(ErrorResponseTO content) implements GetUserApiResponse {}
        record GetUser500ApiResponse(ErrorResponseTO content) implements GetUserApiResponse {}
    }

    sealed interface CreateUserApiResponse {
        record CreateUser201ApiResponse(UserResponseTO content) implements CreateUserApiResponse {}
        record CreateUser400ApiResponse(ErrorResponseTO content) implements CreateUserApiResponse {}
        record CreateUser409ApiResponse(ErrorResponseTO content) implements CreateUserApiResponse {}
    }
}
```

## Response Selection Guide

| HTTP Status | Scenario | Response Class |
|-------------|----------|----------------|
| 200 | Successful GET/PUT/PATCH | `*200ApiResponse(content)` |
| 201 | Successful POST (create) | `*201ApiResponse(content)` |
| 204 | Successful DELETE | `*204ApiResponse()` |
| 400 | Invalid input, business rules | `*400ApiResponse(error)` |
| 404 | Resource not found | `*404ApiResponse(error)` |
| 409 | Conflict (duplicate, version) | `*409ApiResponse(error)` |
| 422 | Semantic validation error | `*422ApiResponse(error)` |
| 500 | Unexpected server error | `*500ApiResponse(error)` |

## Common Response Patterns

### Simple Lookup (200/404)

```java
@Override
public UserApiResponses.GetUserApiResponse getUser(String userId) {
    return userService.findById(userId)
        .<UserApiResponses.GetUserApiResponse>map(user ->
            new UserApiResponses.GetUserApiResponse.GetUser200ApiResponse(
                mapper.toResponse(user)
            )
        )
        .orElseGet(() ->
            new UserApiResponses.GetUserApiResponse.GetUser404ApiResponse(
                new ErrorResponseTO("User not found: " + userId)
            )
        );
}
```

### Create with Validation (201/400/409)

```java
@Override
public UserApiResponses.CreateUserApiResponse createUser(CreateUserRequest request) {
    // Check for duplicates
    if (userService.emailExists(request.email())) {
        return new CreateUser409ApiResponse(
            new ErrorResponseTO("Email already exists: " + request.email())
        );
    }

    // Business rule validation
    if (request.age() != null && request.age() < 18) {
        return new CreateUser400ApiResponse(
            new ErrorResponseTO("User must be at least 18 years old")
        );
    }

    // Create user
    var user = userService.create(mapper.toEntity(request));
    return new CreateUser201ApiResponse(mapper.toResponse(user));
}
```

### Delete (204/404)

```java
@Override
public UserApiResponses.DeleteUserApiResponse deleteUser(String userId) {
    if (!userService.exists(userId)) {
        return new DeleteUser404ApiResponse(
            new ErrorResponseTO("User not found: " + userId)
        );
    }

    userService.delete(userId);
    return new DeleteUser204ApiResponse();  // No content
}
```

### Batch Operation (200 with errors)

```java
@Override
public UserApiResponses.BatchCreateApiResponse batchCreate(BatchCreateRequest request) {
    List<UserResponseTO> created = new ArrayList<>();
    List<ErrorDetailTO> errors = new ArrayList<>();

    for (CreateUserRequest item : request.items()) {
        try {
            var user = userService.create(mapper.toEntity(item));
            created.add(mapper.toResponse(user));
        } catch (EmailAlreadyExistsException e) {
            errors.add(new ErrorDetailTO(item.email(), e.getMessage()));
        }
    }

    return new BatchCreate200ApiResponse(
        new BatchCreateResponseTO(created, errors)
    );
}
```

### With Custom Headers

```yaml
# OpenAPI spec
responses:
  "200":
    description: User found
    headers:
      X-Total-Count:
        schema:
          type: integer
    content:
      application/json:
